Questions:
What is the primary goal of the RADIOCREMVAL research study?
A) To evaluate the effectiveness of a new surgical procedure for head and neck tumors;
B) To develop a new diagnostic imaging technique for carcinoma;
C) To assess the reduction of grade 3-4 acute radiation dermatitis to grade 2 in patients using a protective cream;
D) To compare the outcomes of different chemotherapy drugs on skin health.

Correct answer: C

If you experience any issues or have questions related to the RADIOCREMVAL study, whom should you contact?

A) The hospital's general information desk;
B) Dr. Antonio J. Conde, the principal investigator of the study;
C) The local pharmacy providing the creams;
D) A family member or friend.

Correct answer: B) Dr. Antonio J. Conde, the principal investigator of the study.
